<exercise checkit-seed="0006" checkit-slug="LimitInInf" checkit-title="Limits with infinite inputs">
    <statement>
        <p>
Explain how to find
the value of each limit.
        </p>
        <ol>
                <li><p><me>
\lim_{x\to-\infty } \frac{4 \, {x^5} + 7 \, {x^3} + 3}{2 \, {x^2} + 2 \, {x^6} - 1}
\,\text{ and }\,
\lim_{x\to+\infty } \frac{4 \, {x^5} + 7 \, {x^3} + 3}{2 \, {x^2} + 2 \, {x^6} - 1}
                </me></p></li>
                <li><p><me>
\lim_{x\to-\infty } \frac{2 \, {x^4} + 3 \, {x^3} + 8}{3 \, {x^4} - 5 \, {x^2} + 4}
\,\text{ and }\,
\lim_{x\to+\infty } \frac{2 \, {x^4} + 3 \, {x^3} + 8}{3 \, {x^4} - 5 \, {x^2} + 4}
                </me></p></li>
                <li><p><me>
\lim_{x\to-\infty } \frac{3 \, {x^4} - 9 \, {x^6} + 1}{3 \, {x^5} + 5 \, {x^2} + 3}
\,\text{ and }\,
\lim_{x\to+\infty } \frac{3 \, {x^4} - 9 \, {x^6} + 1}{3 \, {x^5} + 5 \, {x^2} + 3}
                </me></p></li>
        </ol>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <ol>
                <li><p><me>
\lim_{x\to-\infty } \frac{4 \, {x^5} + 7 \, {x^3} + 3}{2 \, {x^2} + 2 \, {x^6} - 1} = 0
\,\text{ and }\,
\lim_{x\to+\infty } \frac{4 \, {x^5} + 7 \, {x^3} + 3}{2 \, {x^2} + 2 \, {x^6} - 1} = 0
                </me></p></li>
                <li><p><me>
\lim_{x\to-\infty } \frac{2 \, {x^4} + 3 \, {x^3} + 8}{3 \, {x^4} - 5 \, {x^2} + 4} = \frac{2}{3}
\,\text{ and }\,
\lim_{x\to+\infty } \frac{2 \, {x^4} + 3 \, {x^3} + 8}{3 \, {x^4} - 5 \, {x^2} + 4} = \frac{2}{3}
                </me></p></li>
                <li><p><me>
\lim_{x\to-\infty } \frac{3 \, {x^4} - 9 \, {x^6} + 1}{3 \, {x^5} + 5 \, {x^2} + 3} = +\infty
\,\text{ and }\,
\lim_{x\to+\infty } \frac{3 \, {x^4} - 9 \, {x^6} + 1}{3 \, {x^5} + 5 \, {x^2} + 3} = -\infty
                </me></p></li>
        </ol>
    </answer>
</exercise>
